> Please merge master and make sure this lemma is next to the one added in #10832

I really don't know how to merge master...

@XavierXarles, I took care of merging master, moving the lemma and adding to doc-strings: I hope that you do not mind!

For future reference, if you use Git from the commandline, "merging master" likely looks as follows:
```bash
git fetch
git merge origin/master
##  maybe fix conflicts -- there were none this time
```

```suggestion
theorem isUnit_iff_exists_and_exists [Monoid M] {a : M} :
```
maybe? `both` isn't really in our naming lexicon.

I would guess you can now inline this as something like
```suggestion
    exact ⟨⟨a, b, hab, left_inv_eq_right_inv hca hab▸ hca⟩, rfl⟩
```
(untested)

```suggestion
    exact ⟨⟨a, b, hab, left_inv_eq_right_inv hca hab ▸ hca⟩, rfl⟩
```
there seem to be only two instances of `▸` not preceded by a space in Mathlib.

I propose one further golf, since some of these deconstruction/construction lemmas already exist!

```suggestion
  refine ⟨fun h => ⟨h.exists_right_inv, h.exists_left_inv⟩, ?_⟩
  rintro ⟨⟨b, hab⟩, ⟨c, hca⟩⟩
  exact ⟨⟨a, b, hab, left_inv_eq_right_inv hca hab ▸ hca⟩, rfl⟩
```
